int arr[]: An integer array used to store elements of the two stacks.
int size: Represents the total size of the array.
int top1, top2: Pointers indicating the top of the first and second stacks respectively.
Initializes the size to 100.
Creates an array of size 100 and sets top1 to -1 (indicating an empty stack1) and top2 to size (indicating an empty stack2 at the end of the array).
Adds an element x to the stack1.
Increments top1 and assigns x to the array at the index top1.
Adds an element x to the stack2.
Decrements top2 and assigns x to the array at the index top2.
